SearchSection.title: Stock1
SearchSection.history: Tulips are a genus of spring-blooming perennial herbaceous bulbiferous geophytes. The flowers are usually large, showy and brightly coloured, generally red, pink, yellow, or white.
SearchSection.percentageDifference: Holland is still the largest producer of tulips
